HEADWORD: Mesoscapula
<hw>Mes`o*scap"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + <ets>scapula</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>A process from the middle of the scapula in some animals; the spine
of the scapula.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

